The paper analyzes the disciplinary coverage of the Thomson Reuters' Book Citation Index database, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The study examines publisher distribution by field and country of publication, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and digital libraries (cs.DL). The focus on disciplinary coverage and specialization is also relevant to the sub-category of library and information science (cs.LIS). The study also mentions errors in the database, which could be of interest to researchers working on data quality and data management (cs.CY). Finally, the study uses descriptive statistics, which is a common method in data science (cs.DS).
